AD_ELEMENT.NAME: Attachment
AD_ELEMENT.HELP: Attachment can be of any document/file type and can be attached to any record in the system.

AD_ELEMENT.NAME: Client
AD_ELEMENT.HELP: A Client is a company or a legal entity. You cannot share data between Clients.

AD_ELEMENT.NAME: Column
AD_ELEMENT.DESCRIPTION: A link to the database column of the table.
AD_ELEMENT.HELP: Link to the database column of the table

AD_ELEMENT.NAME: Displayed Column
AD_ELEMENT.HELP: The Display Column indicates the column that will display.

AD_ELEMENT.NAME: Application Element
AD_ELEMENT.DESCRIPTION: An element that consolidates help, descriptions and terms for a database column and allows for a central maintenance.
AD_ELEMENT.HELP: The System Element allows for the central maintenance of help, descriptions and terminology for a database column.

AD_ELEMENT.NAME: Field
AD_ELEMENT.DESCRIPTION: Any element which can be viewed, edited, or added to a window.
AD_ELEMENT.HELP: The Field identifies a field on a database table.

AD_ELEMENT.NAME: Key Column
AD_ELEMENT.HELP: The Key Column indicates that this the unique identifier of a record on this table.

AD_ELEMENT.NAME: Language
AD_ELEMENT.DESCRIPTION: A method of communication being used.
AD_ELEMENT.HELP: The Language identifies the language to use for display

AD_ELEMENT.NAME: Menu
AD_ELEMENT.HELP: The Menu identifies a unique Menu. Menus are used to control the display of those screens a user has access to.

AD_ELEMENT.NAME: Trx Organization
AD_ELEMENT.DESCRIPTION: The organization which performs or initiates the transaction.
AD_ELEMENT.HELP: The organization which performs or initiates this transaction (for another organization). The owning Organization may not be the transaction organization in a service bureau environment, with centralized services, and inter-organization transactions.

AD_ELEMENT.NAME: Organization
AD_ELEMENT.HELP: An organization is a unit of your client or legal entity - examples are store, department. You can share data between organizations.

AD_ELEMENT.NAME: Process Instance
AD_ELEMENT.HELP: Process Instance identifies the instance of a process. Every time a process is executed a new instance of it is created.

AD_ELEMENT.NAME: Preference
AD_ELEMENT.HELP: Personal Preference, a default value that will be used by a user.

AD_ELEMENT.NAME: Process
AD_ELEMENT.DESCRIPTION: A series of actions carried out in sequential order.
AD_ELEMENT.HELP: The Process field identifies a unique Process or Report in the system.

AD_ELEMENT.NAME: Process Parameter
AD_ELEMENT.HELP: Process Parameter identifies the parameters of a process or report.

AD_ELEMENT.NAME: List Reference
AD_ELEMENT.HELP: The Reference List field indicates a list of reference values from a database tables. Reference lists populate drop down list boxes in data entry screens

AD_ELEMENT.NAME: Reference
AD_ELEMENT.DESCRIPTION: The data type of this field.
AD_ELEMENT.HELP: The Reference indicates the type of reference field

AD_ELEMENT.NAME: Reference Search Key
AD_ELEMENT.DESCRIPTION: The exact reference specification for a list or a table.
AD_ELEMENT.HELP: The Reference Value indicates where the reference values are stored. It must be specified if the data type is Table or List.

AD_ELEMENT.NAME: Role
AD_ELEMENT.DESCRIPTION: The profile of security for the user defining what windows and tabs they can see.
AD_ELEMENT.HELP: The Role determines security and access a user who has this Role will have in the System.

AD_ELEMENT.NAME: Sequence
AD_ELEMENT.DESCRIPTION: The order of records in a specified document.
AD_ELEMENT.HELP: The Sequence defines the numbering sequence to be used for documents.

AD_ELEMENT.NAME: Tab
AD_ELEMENT.DESCRIPTION: An indication that a tab is displayed within a window.
AD_ELEMENT.HELP: The Tab indicates a tab that displays within a window.

AD_ELEMENT.NAME: Table
AD_ELEMENT.DESCRIPTION: A dictionary table used for this tab that points to the database table.
AD_ELEMENT.HELP: The Table indicates the table in which a field or fields reside.

AD_ELEMENT.NAME: OS Task
AD_ELEMENT.DESCRIPTION: The name of an operating task.
AD_ELEMENT.HELP: The Task field identifies a Operation System Task in the system.

AD_ELEMENT.NAME: Primary Tree BPartner
AD_ELEMENT.HELP: Business Partner Tree

AD_ELEMENT.NAME: Tree
AD_ELEMENT.HELP: The Tree field identifies a unique Tree in the system. Trees define roll ups or summary levels of information. They are used in reports for defining report points and summarization levels.

AD_ELEMENT.NAME: Primary Tree Menu
AD_ELEMENT.HELP: Tree Menu

AD_ELEMENT.NAME: Primary Tree Organization
AD_ELEMENT.HELP: Organization Tree

AD_ELEMENT.NAME: Primary Tree Product
AD_ELEMENT.HELP: Product Tree

AD_ELEMENT.NAME: Primary Tree Project
AD_ELEMENT.HELP: Project Tree

AD_ELEMENT.NAME: User/Contact
AD_ELEMENT.DESCRIPTION: An acquaintance to reach for information related to the business partner.
AD_ELEMENT.HELP: The User identifies a unique user in the system. This could be an internal user or a business partner contact

AD_ELEMENT.NAME: Validation
AD_ELEMENT.DESCRIPTION: A validation rule that defines how an entry is determined to be valid or invalid.
AD_ELEMENT.HELP: The Validation Rule indicates a unique validation rule. These rules define how an entry is determined to valid or invalid.

AD_ELEMENT.NAME: Instance
AD_ELEMENT.HELP: Workflow Instance

AD_ELEMENT.NAME: Next Node
AD_ELEMENT.HELP: The Next Node indicates the next step or task in this Workflow.

AD_ELEMENT.NAME: Node
AD_ELEMENT.DESCRIPTION: The connecting points in a workflow.
AD_ELEMENT.HELP: The Workflow Node indicates a unique step or process in a Workflow.

AD_ELEMENT.NAME: Window
AD_ELEMENT.DESCRIPTION: A work area which can be used to create, view, edit, and process a record.
AD_ELEMENT.HELP: The Window field identifies a unique Window in the system.

AD_ELEMENT.NAME: Workflow
AD_ELEMENT.DESCRIPTION: A set of procedures used to show the path to complete a specified task.
AD_ELEMENT.HELP: The Workflow field identifies a unique Workflow in the system.

AD_ELEMENT.NAME: Data Access Level
AD_ELEMENT.DESCRIPTION: A privilege required to make adjustments to an object.
AD_ELEMENT.HELP: Indicates the access level required for this record or process.

AD_ELEMENT.NAME: Account Sign
AD_ELEMENT.DESCRIPTION: Indicates the Natural Sign of the Account as a Debit or Credit
AD_ELEMENT.HELP: Indicates if the expected balance for this account should be a Debit or a Credit.

AD_ELEMENT.NAME: Account Type
AD_ELEMENT.HELP: Valid account types are A - Asset, E - Expense, L - Liability, O- Owner Equity, R -Revenue and M- Memo. The account type is used to determine what taxes, if any are applicable, validating payables and receivables for business partners. Note: Memo account amounts are ignored when checking for balancing

AD_ELEMENT.NAME: Account
AD_ELEMENT.DESCRIPTION: The identification code used for accounting.
AD_ELEMENT.HELP: The (natural) account used

AD_ELEMENT.NAME: Second Accounting Schema
AD_ELEMENT.DESCRIPTION: For parallel reporting using different accounting currency or field selection
AD_ELEMENT.HELP: The Second Accounting Schema indicates an alternate set of rules to use for generating reports.

AD_ELEMENT.NAME: Third Accounting Schema
AD_ELEMENT.DESCRIPTION: For parallel reporting using different accounting currency or field selection
AD_ELEMENT.HELP: The Third Accounting Schema indicates an alternate set of rules to use for generating reports.

AD_ELEMENT.NAME: Acquisition Cost
AD_ELEMENT.DESCRIPTION: The cost of gaining the prospect as a customer
AD_ELEMENT.HELP: The Acquisition Cost identifies the cost associated with making this prospect a customer.

AD_ELEMENT.NAME: Action
AD_ELEMENT.DESCRIPTION: A drop down list box indicating the next step to take.
AD_ELEMENT.HELP: The Action field indicates the Action to be performed for this element.

AD_ELEMENT.NAME: Lifetime Revenue to Date
AD_ELEMENT.HELP: The Actual Life Time Value is the recorded revenue to be generated by this Business Partner.

AD_ELEMENT.NAME: Additional Tree (1)
AD_ELEMENT.HELP: The Additional Tree is used to define alternate roll ups which can be used in reporting. For example, you may have a Business Partner Tree which rolls up based on geographic location and an additional tree which rolls up based on industry.

AD_ELEMENT.NAME: Additional Tree (2)
AD_ELEMENT.HELP: The Additional Tree is used to define alternate roll ups which can be used in reporting. For example, you may have a Business Partner Tree which rolls up based on geographic location and an additional tree which rolls up based on industry.

AD_ELEMENT.NAME: Address Line 1
AD_ELEMENT.DESCRIPTION: A space to write the location of a business partner.
AD_ELEMENT.HELP: The Address 1 identifies the address for an entity's location

AD_ELEMENT.NAME: Address Line 2
AD_ELEMENT.DESCRIPTION: A space to write the location of a business partner.
AD_ELEMENT.HELP: The Address 2 provides additional address information for an entity. It can be used for building location, apartment number or similar information.

AD_ELEMENT.NAME: After Delivery
AD_ELEMENT.DESCRIPTION: Due after delivery rather than after invoicing
AD_ELEMENT.HELP: The After Delivery checkbox indicates that payment is due after delivery as opposed to after invoicing.

AD_ELEMENT.NAME: Alias
AD_ELEMENT.DESCRIPTION: Defines an alternate method of indicating an account combination.
AD_ELEMENT.HELP: The Alias field allows you to define a alternate method for referring to a full account combination. For example, the Account Receivable Account for Garden World may be aliased as GW_AR.

AD_ELEMENT.NAME: Amount
AD_ELEMENT.DESCRIPTION: A monetary sum of two or more quantities.

AD_ELEMENT.NAME: Credit
AD_ELEMENT.DESCRIPTION: The amount credited to an account, converted to the organization default currency.
AD_ELEMENT.HELP: The Account Credit Amount indicates the transaction amount converted to this organization's accounting currency

AD_ELEMENT.NAME: Debit
AD_ELEMENT.DESCRIPTION: The amount debited to an account, converted to the organization default currency.
AD_ELEMENT.HELP: The Account Debit Amount indicates the transaction amount converted to this organization's accounting currency

AD_ELEMENT.NAME: Approval Amount
AD_ELEMENT.DESCRIPTION: The approval amount limit for this role
AD_ELEMENT.HELP: The Approval Amount field indicates the amount limit this Role has for approval of documents.

AD_ELEMENT.NAME: Foriegn Currency Credit
AD_ELEMENT.DESCRIPTION: The amount credited from the account, given in provider currency.
AD_ELEMENT.HELP: The Source Credit Amount indicates the credit amount for this line in the source currency.

AD_ELEMENT.NAME: Foriegn Currency Debit
AD_ELEMENT.DESCRIPTION: The amount debited from the account, given in provider currency.
AD_ELEMENT.HELP: The Source Debit Amount indicates the credit amount for this line in the source currency.

AD_ELEMENT.NAME: Attribute
AD_ELEMENT.DESCRIPTION: A defined characteristic of a specific product.
AD_ELEMENT.HELP: Attribute name that will take the value.

AD_ELEMENT.NAME: Automatic Period Control
AD_ELEMENT.DESCRIPTION: If selected, the periods are automatically opened and closed
AD_ELEMENT.HELP: In the Automatic Period Control, periods are opened and closed based on the current date. If the Manual alternative is activated, you have to open and close periods explicitly.

AD_ELEMENT.NAME: Batch Sequence
AD_ELEMENT.HELP: Document Sequence for Batch

AD_ELEMENT.NAME: Invoice Address
AD_ELEMENT.DESCRIPTION: The location where the invoice payment request will be sent.
AD_ELEMENT.HELP: An indication of the address to use in the invoice.
AD_ELEMENT.PO_HELP: The Bill/Invoice From indicated the address where the invoice is created by the vendor

AD_ELEMENT.NAME: Bindary Data
AD_ELEMENT.HELP: The Binary field stores binary data.

AD_ELEMENT.NAME: Budget Status
AD_ELEMENT.DESCRIPTION: Indicates the current status of this budget
AD_ELEMENT.HELP: The Budget Status indicates the current status of this budget (i.e Draft, Approved)

AD_ELEMENT.NAME: Primary Accounting Schema
AD_ELEMENT.HELP: An Accounting Schema defines the rules used accounting such as costing method, currency and calendar.

AD_ELEMENT.NAME: Second Accounting Schema
AD_ELEMENT.HELP: An Accounting Schema defines the rules used in accounting such as costing method, currency and calendar.

AD_ELEMENT.NAME: Third Accounting Schema
AD_ELEMENT.HELP: An Accounting Schema defines the rules used in accounting such as costing method, currency and calendar

AD_ELEMENT.NAME: Acct.Schema Element
AD_ELEMENT.HELP: The Account Schema Element defines each element that comprise the account key.

AD_ELEMENT.NAME: Accounting Schema
AD_ELEMENT.DESCRIPTION: The structure used in accounting including costing methods, currencies, and the calendar.
AD_ELEMENT.HELP: An Accounting Schema defines the rules used in accounting such as costing method, currency and calendar

AD_ELEMENT.NAME: Approval
AD_ELEMENT.HELP: The Approval indicates the type of approval. This field is displayed only if the Approved checkbox has been selected

AD_ELEMENT.NAME: Business Partner
AD_ELEMENT.DESCRIPTION: Anyone who takes part in daily business operations by acting as a customer, employee, etc.
AD_ELEMENT.HELP: A Business Partner is anyone with whom you transact. This can include Vendor, Customer, Employee or Salesperson

AD_ELEMENT.NAME: Partner Address
AD_ELEMENT.DESCRIPTION: The location of the selected business partner.
AD_ELEMENT.HELP: The Partner address indicates the location of a Business Partner
AD_ELEMENT.PO_DESCRIPTION: Identifies the (ship from) address for this Business Partner
AD_ELEMENT.PO_HELP: The Partner address indicates the location of a Business Partner

AD_ELEMENT.NAME: Calendar
AD_ELEMENT.DESCRIPTION: A table showing the days of the week for each month of the year.
AD_ELEMENT.HELP: The Calendar uniquely identifies an accounting calendar. Multiple calendars can be used. For example you may need a standard calendar that runs from Jan 1 to Dec 31 and a fiscal calendar that runs from July 1 to June 30.

AD_ELEMENT.NAME: Conversion Rate
AD_ELEMENT.DESCRIPTION: The amount or quantity at which one unit of measure is changed to another.
AD_ELEMENT.HELP: The Conversion Rate defines the rate (multiply or divide) to use when converting a source currency to an accounting currency.

AD_ELEMENT.NAME: Country
AD_ELEMENT.HELP: The Country defines a Country. Each Country must be defined before it can be used in any document.

AD_ELEMENT.NAME: Currency
AD_ELEMENT.DESCRIPTION: An accepted medium of monetary exchange that may vary across countries.
AD_ELEMENT.HELP: Indicates the Currency to be used when processing or reporting on this record

AD_ELEMENT.NAME: To Currency
AD_ELEMENT.HELP: The Currency To defines the target currency for this conversion rate.

AD_ELEMENT.NAME: Document Type
AD_ELEMENT.DESCRIPTION: A value defining what sequence and process setup are used to handle this document.
AD_ELEMENT.HELP: The Document Type determines document sequence and processing rules

AD_ELEMENT.NAME: Transaction Document
AD_ELEMENT.DESCRIPTION: The specific document type which should be used for a specified transaction.
AD_ELEMENT.HELP: You can convert document types (e.g. from Offer to Order or Invoice). The conversion is then reflected in the current type. This processing is initiated by selecting the appropriate Document Action.

AD_ELEMENT.NAME: Account Element
AD_ELEMENT.DESCRIPTION: A identification code for an account type.
AD_ELEMENT.HELP: Account Elements can be natural accounts or user defined values.

AD_ELEMENT.NAME: Accounting Element
AD_ELEMENT.DESCRIPTION: A unique identifier for an account type.
AD_ELEMENT.HELP: The Account Element uniquely identifies an Account Type. These are commonly known as a Chart of Accounts.

AD_ELEMENT.NAME: Location from Address
AD_ELEMENT.DESCRIPTION: The location where items are sent from.
AD_ELEMENT.HELP: The Location From indicates the location that a product was moved from.

AD_ELEMENT.NAME: Location to Address
AD_ELEMENT.DESCRIPTION: The location where items are sent to.
AD_ELEMENT.HELP: The Location To indicates the location that a product was moved to.

AD_ELEMENT.NAME: Location / Address
AD_ELEMENT.HELP: The Location / Address field defines the location of an entity.

AD_ELEMENT.NAME: Non Business Day
AD_ELEMENT.DESCRIPTION: Day on which business is not transacted
AD_ELEMENT.HELP: The Non Business Day identifies a day that should not be considered a day when business is transacted

AD_ELEMENT.NAME: Payment Terms
AD_ELEMENT.DESCRIPTION: The setup and timing defined to complete a specified payment.
AD_ELEMENT.HELP: Payment Terms identify the method and timing of payment for this transaction.

AD_ELEMENT.NAME: Period Control
AD_ELEMENT.HELP: The Period Control shows the status of a Period (Never Opened, Opened, Closed) for each of the DocBaseTypes.

AD_ELEMENT.NAME: Period
AD_ELEMENT.HELP: The Period indicates an exclusive range of dates for a calendar.

AD_ELEMENT.NAME: Project
AD_ELEMENT.HELP: Project ID is a user defined identifier for a Project

AD_ELEMENT.NAME: Region
AD_ELEMENT.DESCRIPTION: An area of a specific country.
AD_ELEMENT.HELP: The Region identifies a unique Region for this Country.

AD_ELEMENT.NAME: Sales Region
AD_ELEMENT.DESCRIPTION: A defined section of the world where sales efforts will be focused.
AD_ELEMENT.HELP: The Sales Region indicates a specific area of sales coverage.

AD_ELEMENT.NAME: Tax Category
AD_ELEMENT.DESCRIPTION: A classification of tax options based on similar characteristics or attributes.
AD_ELEMENT.HELP: The Tax Category provides a method of grouping similar taxes. For example, Sales Tax or Value Added Tax.

AD_ELEMENT.NAME: Tax
AD_ELEMENT.DESCRIPTION: The percentage of money requested by the government for this specified product or transaction.
AD_ELEMENT.HELP: The Tax indicates the type of tax for this document line.

AD_ELEMENT.NAME: UOM Conversion
AD_ELEMENT.HELP: The UOM Conversion identifies a unique to and from Unit of Measure, conversion rate and conversion date range.

AD_ELEMENT.NAME: UOM
AD_ELEMENT.DESCRIPTION: A non monetary unit of measure.
AD_ELEMENT.HELP: The UOM defines a unique non monetary Unit of Measure

AD_ELEMENT.NAME: To UOM
AD_ELEMENT.DESCRIPTION: Target or destination Unit of Measure
AD_ELEMENT.HELP: The UOM To indicates the destination UOM for a UOM Conversion pair.

AD_ELEMENT.NAME: UOM for Length
AD_ELEMENT.DESCRIPTION: Standard Unit of Measure for Length
AD_ELEMENT.HELP: The Standard UOM for Length indicates the UOM to use for products referenced by length in a document.

AD_ELEMENT.NAME: UOM for Time
AD_ELEMENT.DESCRIPTION: Standard Unit of Measure for Time
AD_ELEMENT.HELP: The Standard UOM for Time indicates the UOM to use for products referenced by time in a document.

AD_ELEMENT.NAME: UOM for Volume
AD_ELEMENT.DESCRIPTION: Standard Unit of Measure for Volume
AD_ELEMENT.HELP: The Standard UOM for Volume indicates the UOM to use for products referenced by volume in a document.

AD_ELEMENT.NAME: UOM for Weight
AD_ELEMENT.DESCRIPTION: Standard Unit of Measure for Weight
AD_ELEMENT.HELP: The Standard UOM for Weight indicates the UOM to use for products referenced by weight in a document.

AD_ELEMENT.NAME: Accounting Combination
AD_ELEMENT.DESCRIPTION: An identification code comprised of an individual account number and additional dimensions such organization, product, and business partner.
AD_ELEMENT.HELP: The Combination identifies a valid combination of element which represent a GL account.

AD_ELEMENT.NAME: Year
AD_ELEMENT.HELP: The Year uniquely identifies an accounting year for a calendar.

AD_ELEMENT.NAME: Callout
AD_ELEMENT.DESCRIPTION: A series of actions that occur when data is modified.
AD_ELEMENT.HELP: Function Calls separated by semicolons; SE_/SL_/UE_/UL_ - 1st: System/User; 2nd: Enter/Leave; 3rd: _ Underscore, - then Function Name

AD_ELEMENT.NAME: City
AD_ELEMENT.DESCRIPTION: A populated defined area located within a larger area such as a state, province, or country.
AD_ELEMENT.HELP: The City identifies a unique City for this Country or Region.

AD_ELEMENT.NAME: Client List
AD_ELEMENT.HELP: Indicates the Clients (by client id) that this Role can access. Multiple Clients are delimited by a comma ','.

AD_ELEMENT.NAME: Validation Code
AD_ELEMENT.DESCRIPTION: The code that will be executed to determine the setup procedure.
AD_ELEMENT.HELP: The Validation Code is the code that will be executed to determine the rule.

AD_ELEMENT.NAME: DB Column Name
AD_ELEMENT.DESCRIPTION: The name of a column within the database.
AD_ELEMENT.HELP: The Column Name indicates the name of a column on a table as defined in the database.

AD_ELEMENT.NAME: Combination
AD_ELEMENT.HELP: The Combination field defines the unique combination of element values which comprise this account.

AD_ELEMENT.NAME: Comments
AD_ELEMENT.DESCRIPTION: A space to write additional related information.
AD_ELEMENT.HELP: The Comments field allows for free form entry of additional information.

AD_ELEMENT.NAME: Confirmation Message
AD_ELEMENT.DESCRIPTION: A warning or information displayed when saving the record.
AD_ELEMENT.HELP: Warning or information displayed when committing the record

AD_ELEMENT.NAME: Required Condition
AD_ELEMENT.DESCRIPTION: Condition required for workflow to proceed
AD_ELEMENT.HELP: The Condition field identifies the condition that must be met before the Workflow can proceed to the next task.

AD_ELEMENT.NAME: Control Amount
AD_ELEMENT.DESCRIPTION: If not zero, the Debit amount of the document must be equal this amount
AD_ELEMENT.HELP: If the control amount is zero, no check is performed.Otherwise the total Debit amount must be equal to the control amount, before the document is processed.

AD_ELEMENT.NAME: Conversion Rate Type
AD_ELEMENT.DESCRIPTION: A distinct conversion rate characteristic used for processes.
AD_ELEMENT.HELP: The Conversion Rate Type indicates the type of conversion rate. This allows you to enter multiple rates for the same currency pair. For example, one rate may be used for Spot conversions and a different rate for Revaluations.

AD_ELEMENT.NAME: Average Cost
AD_ELEMENT.HELP: Weighted average (actual) costs

AD_ELEMENT.NAME: Standard Cost
AD_ELEMENT.HELP: Standard (plan) costs.

AD_ELEMENT.NAME: Costing Method
AD_ELEMENT.DESCRIPTION: Indicates how Costs will be calculated
AD_ELEMENT.HELP: The Costing Method indicates how costs will be calculated (Standard, Average)

AD_ELEMENT.NAME: Costing Precision
AD_ELEMENT.HELP: The Costing Precision defines the number of decimal places that amounts will be rounded to when performing costing calculations.

AD_ELEMENT.NAME: Costs
AD_ELEMENT.HELP: The Costs indicates the cost of a campaign in an Organizations accounting currency.

AD_ELEMENT.NAME: ISO Country Code
AD_ELEMENT.DESCRIPTION: The geographic country code for a country based on the ISO standard.
AD_ELEMENT.HELP: For details - http://www.din.de/gremien/nas/nabd/iso3166ma/codlstp1.html or - http://www.unece.org/trade/rec/rec03en.htm

AD_ELEMENT.NAME: Creation Date
AD_ELEMENT.DESCRIPTION: The date that this record is completed.
AD_ELEMENT.HELP: The Created field indicates the date that this record was created.

AD_ELEMENT.NAME: Created By
AD_ELEMENT.HELP: The Created By field indicates the user who created this record.

AD_ELEMENT.NAME: Credit Card No.
AD_ELEMENT.HELP: The Credit Card number indicates the number on the credit card, without blanks or spaces.

AD_ELEMENT.NAME: Symbol
AD_ELEMENT.DESCRIPTION: An abbreviated description used to define a unit of measure or currency.
AD_ELEMENT.HELP: The Currency Symbol defines the symbol that will print when this currency is used.

AD_ELEMENT.NAME: Currency Balancing Acct.
AD_ELEMENT.DESCRIPTION: Account used when a currency is out of balance
AD_ELEMENT.HELP: The Currency Balancing Account indicates the account to used when a currency is out of balance (generally due to rounding)

AD_ELEMENT.NAME: Rate
AD_ELEMENT.DESCRIPTION: The percentage to be multiplied by the source to arrive at the tax or exchange amount.
AD_ELEMENT.HELP: The Currency Conversion Rate indicates the rate to use when converting the source currency to the accounting currency

AD_ELEMENT.NAME: Currency Rate Type
AD_ELEMENT.DESCRIPTION: A distinct currency rate characteristic used for processes.
AD_ELEMENT.HELP: The Conversion Rate Type indicates the type of rate to use when retrieving the conversion rate. It allows you to define multiple rates for the same to and from currency. For example you may have a set of rates used for daily transactions with a rate type of SPOT and rates for currency revaluation defined as REVAL.

AD_ELEMENT.NAME: Next Assigned Number
AD_ELEMENT.DESCRIPTION: The next number that will be assigned to an item.
AD_ELEMENT.HELP: The Current Next indicates the next number to use for this document

AD_ELEMENT.NAME: D-U-N-S
AD_ELEMENT.HELP: Used for EDI - For details see www.dnb.com/dunsno/list.htm

AD_ELEMENT.NAME: Non Business Day
AD_ELEMENT.DESCRIPTION: Date when business is not conducted
AD_ELEMENT.HELP: The Date field identifies a calendar date on which business will not be conducted.

AD_ELEMENT.NAME: Accounting Date
AD_ELEMENT.DESCRIPTION: The date this transaction is recorded in the general ledger.
AD_ELEMENT.HELP: The Accounting Date indicates the date to be used on the General Ledger account entries generated from this document

AD_ELEMENT.NAME: Date Delivered
AD_ELEMENT.DESCRIPTION: Date when the product was delivered
AD_ELEMENT.HELP: Date when the product was delivered

AD_ELEMENT.NAME: Document Date
AD_ELEMENT.DESCRIPTION: The time listed on the document.
AD_ELEMENT.HELP: The Document Date indicates the date the document was generated. It may or may not be the same as the accounting date.

AD_ELEMENT.NAME: Invoice Date
AD_ELEMENT.DESCRIPTION: The time listed on the invoice.
AD_ELEMENT.HELP: The Date Invoice indicates the date printed on the invoice.

AD_ELEMENT.NAME: Order Date
AD_ELEMENT.DESCRIPTION: The time listed on the order.
AD_ELEMENT.HELP: Indicates the Date an item was ordered.

AD_ELEMENT.NAME: Scheduled Delivery Date
AD_ELEMENT.DESCRIPTION: The date that a task, process, or action is to be completed or delivered by.
AD_ELEMENT.HELP: The Date Promised indicates the date, if any, that an Order was promised for.

AD_ELEMENT.NAME: Default Value
AD_ELEMENT.DESCRIPTION: The first non-null value in a set of values. It is used as a default value for a field when creating a record.
AD_ELEMENT.HELP: The defaults are evaluated in the order of definition, the first not null value becomes the default value of the column. The values are separated by comma or semicolon. a) Literals:. 'Text' or 123 b) Variables - in format @Variable@ - Login e.g. #Date, #AD_Org_ID, #AD_Client_ID - Accounting Schema: e.g. $C_AcctSchema_ID, $C_Calendar_ID - Global defaults: e.g. DateFormat - Window values (all Picks, CheckBoxes, RadioButtons, and DateDoc/DateAcct) c) SQL code with the tag: @SQL=SELECT something AS DefaultValue FROM ... The SQL statement can contain variables. There can be no other value other than the SQL statement. The default is only evaluated, if no user preference is defined. Default definitions are ignored for record columns as Key, Parent, Client as well as Buttons.

AD_ELEMENT.NAME: Delivery Method
AD_ELEMENT.DESCRIPTION: The desired means of getting requested goods to a business partner.
AD_ELEMENT.HELP: The Delivery Via indicates how the products should be delivered. For example, will the order be picked up or shipped.

AD_ELEMENT.NAME: Description
AD_ELEMENT.DESCRIPTION: A space to write additional related information.
AD_ELEMENT.HELP: A description is limited to 255 characters.

AD_ELEMENT.NAME: Discontinued
AD_ELEMENT.DESCRIPTION: A statement mentioning that this product will no longer be available on the market.
AD_ELEMENT.HELP: The Discontinued check box indicates a product that has been discontinued.

AD_ELEMENT.NAME: Discontinued by
AD_ELEMENT.DESCRIPTION: The name of the person who discontinues an item.
AD_ELEMENT.HELP: The Discontinued By indicates the individual who discontinued this product

AD_ELEMENT.NAME: Discount %
AD_ELEMENT.DESCRIPTION: The proportional discount given to an item, without respect to any previously defined discounts.
AD_ELEMENT.HELP: The Discount indicates the discount applied or taken as a percentage.

AD_ELEMENT.NAME: Discount Days
AD_ELEMENT.DESCRIPTION: Number of days from invoice date to be eligible for discount
AD_ELEMENT.HELP: The Discount Days indicates the number of days that payment must be received in to be eligible for the stated discount.

AD_ELEMENT.NAME: Displayed Length
AD_ELEMENT.DESCRIPTION: The number of characters that made be added to a specified field.
AD_ELEMENT.HELP: Display length is the size that will be appear for the field, it can be different that the actual size of the column (note that if it is bigger than the column the data will be truncated to the column size).

AD_ELEMENT.NAME: Display Logic
AD_ELEMENT.DESCRIPTION: A specification of statements which, when evaluated as false, are required to hide the field.
AD_ELEMENT.HELP: A specification of statements which, when evaluated as false, are required to hide the field.

AD_ELEMENT.NAME: Displayed Value
AD_ELEMENT.DESCRIPTION: Displays Value column with the Display column
AD_ELEMENT.HELP: The Display Value checkbox indicates if the value column will display with the display column.

AD_ELEMENT.NAME: Address Print Format
AD_ELEMENT.HELP: The Address Print format defines the format to be used when this address prints. The following notations are used: @C@=City @P@=Postal @A@=PostalAdd @R@=Region

AD_ELEMENT.NAME: Divide Rate by
AD_ELEMENT.DESCRIPTION: The rate by which the base unit will be divided by to create the converted unit.
AD_ELEMENT.HELP: To convert Source number to Target number, the Source is divided by the divide rate. If you enter a Divide Rate, the Multiply Rate will be automatically calculated.

AD_ELEMENT.NAME: Document Action
AD_ELEMENT.DESCRIPTION: A means of changing the transaction status of the document.
AD_ELEMENT.HELP: You find the current status in the Document Status field. The options are listed in a popup

AD_ELEMENT.NAME: Document Sequence
AD_ELEMENT.DESCRIPTION: Document sequence determines the numbering of documents
AD_ELEMENT.HELP: The Document Sequence indicates the sequencing rule to use for this document type.

AD_ELEMENT.NAME: Document Status
AD_ELEMENT.DESCRIPTION: A specified position resulting from processes which have/have not been executed.
AD_ELEMENT.HELP: The Document Status indicates the status of a document at this time. If you want to change the document status, use the Document Action field

AD_ELEMENT.NAME: Document No.
AD_ELEMENT.DESCRIPTION: An often automatically generated identifier for all documents.
AD_ELEMENT.HELP: The document number is usually automatically generated by the system and determined by the document type of the document. If the document is not saved, the preliminary number is displayed in "<>".If the document type of your document has no automatic document sequence defined, the field is empty if you create a new document. This is for documents which usually have an external number (like vendor invoice). If you leave the field empty, the system will generate a document number for you. The document sequence used for this fallback number is defined in the "Maintain Sequence" window with the name "DocumentNo_<TableName>", where TableName is the actual name of the table (e.g. C_Order).

AD_ELEMENT.NAME: EMU Entry Date
AD_ELEMENT.DESCRIPTION: Date when the currency joined / will join the EMU
AD_ELEMENT.HELP: The EMU Entry Date defines the date that this currency entered, or will enter the Economic Monetary Union.

AD_ELEMENT.NAME: EMU Rate
AD_ELEMENT.HELP: The EMU Rate defines the official rate to be used when converting from this currency to the Euro.

AD_ELEMENT.NAME: Type
AD_ELEMENT.DESCRIPTION: A distinct item characteristic used for processes and sometimes grouped within a category.
AD_ELEMENT.HELP: The Element Type indicates if this element is the Account element or is a User Defined element.

AD_ELEMENT.NAME: Ending Date
AD_ELEMENT.DESCRIPTION: A parameter stating when a specified request will end.
AD_ELEMENT.HELP: The End Date indicates the last date in this range.

AD_ELEMENT.NAME: Phone No. Format
AD_ELEMENT.HELP: Phone Format

AD_ELEMENT.NAME: Postal Code Format
AD_ELEMENT.HELP: Postal code Format

AD_ELEMENT.NAME: Additional Postal Format
AD_ELEMENT.HELP: Additional Postal Format

AD_ELEMENT.DESCRIPTION: A fax number for a specified business partner.
AD_ELEMENT.HELP: The Fax identifies a facsimile number for this Business Partner or Location

AD_ELEMENT.NAME: Length
AD_ELEMENT.DESCRIPTION: An indication of the column length as defined in the database.
AD_ELEMENT.HELP: The Length indicates the length of a column as defined in the database.

AD_ELEMENT.NAME: Date of First Sale
AD_ELEMENT.HELP: The First Sale Date identifies the date of the first sale to this Business Partner

AD_ELEMENT.NAME: Freight Amount
AD_ELEMENT.DESCRIPTION: The charge amount for a specified shipment.
AD_ELEMENT.HELP: The Freight Amount indicates the amount charged for Freight in the document currency.

AD_ELEMENT.NAME: GAAP
AD_ELEMENT.HELP: The GAAP identifies the account principles that this accounting schema will adhere to.

AD_ELEMENT.NAME: Budget
AD_ELEMENT.DESCRIPTION: A group of planned expenses for a task.
AD_ELEMENT.HELP: The General Ledger Budget identifies a user defined budget. These can be used in reporting as a comparison against your actual amounts.

AD_ELEMENT.NAME: G/L Category
AD_ELEMENT.DESCRIPTION: A classification used to group lines in the general ledger.
AD_ELEMENT.HELP: The General Ledger Category is an optional, user defined method of grouping journal lines.

AD_ELEMENT.NAME: Journal Batch
AD_ELEMENT.HELP: The General Ledger Journal Batch identifies a group of journals to be processed as a group.

AD_ELEMENT.NAME: Journal Line
AD_ELEMENT.HELP: The General Ledger Journal Line identifies a single transaction in a journal.

AD_ELEMENT.NAME: Journal Entry
AD_ELEMENT.DESCRIPTION: One transaction with a debit and credit and entered into the general ledger.
AD_ELEMENT.HELP: The General Ledger Journal identifies a group of journal lines which represent a logical business transaction

AD_ELEMENT.NAME: Grand Total Amount
AD_ELEMENT.DESCRIPTION: The final monetary amount (including taxes) charge listed in a document.
AD_ELEMENT.HELP: The Grand Total displays the total amount including Tax and Freight in document currency

AD_ELEMENT.NAME: Use Account Alias
AD_ELEMENT.DESCRIPTION: Ability to select (partial) account combinations by an Alias
AD_ELEMENT.HELP: The Alias checkbox indicates that account combination can be selected using a user defined alias or short key.

AD_ELEMENT.NAME: Use Account Combination Control
AD_ELEMENT.DESCRIPTION: Combination of account elements are checked
AD_ELEMENT.HELP: The Combination Control checkbox indicates if the combination of account elements will be verified against the defined acceptable combination.

AD_ELEMENT.NAME: Additional Postal Code
AD_ELEMENT.HELP: The Additional Postal Code checkbox indicates if this address uses an additional Postal Code. If it is selected an additional field displays for entry of the additional Postal Code.

AD_ELEMENT.NAME: Has Regions
AD_ELEMENT.HELP: The Country has Region checkbox is selected if the Country being defined is divided into regions. If this checkbox is selected, the Region Tab is accessible.

AD_ELEMENT.NAME: Tree Included
AD_ELEMENT.HELP: The Has Tree checkbox indicates if this window displays a tree metaphor.

AD_ELEMENT.NAME: Help/Comment
AD_ELEMENT.DESCRIPTION: A comment that adds additional information to help users work with fields.
AD_ELEMENT.HELP: The Help field contains a hint, comment or help about the use of this item.

AD_ELEMENT.NAME: ISDN
AD_ELEMENT.HELP: The ISDN identifies a ISDN or Modem line number.

AD_ELEMENT.NAME: ISO Code
AD_ELEMENT.HELP: For details - http://www.unece.org/trade/rec/rec09en.htm

AD_ELEMENT.NAME: Income Summary
AD_ELEMENT.HELP: Account used for income summary

AD_ELEMENT.NAME: Increment By
AD_ELEMENT.DESCRIPTION: An addition to a starting number by a specified value.
AD_ELEMENT.HELP: The Increment indicates the number to increment the last document number by to arrive at the next sequence number

AD_ELEMENT.NAME: Due from Intercompany
AD_ELEMENT.HELP: The Intercompany Due From account indicates the account that represents money owed to this organization from other organizations.

AD_ELEMENT.NAME: Due to Intercompany
AD_ELEMENT.HELP: The Intercompany Due To Account indicates the account that represents money owed to other organizations.

AD_ELEMENT.NAME: Day of the Month
AD_ELEMENT.HELP: The Invoice Day indicates the day of invoice generation. If twice monthly, the second time is 15 days after this day.

AD_ELEMENT.NAME: Invoice Frequency
AD_ELEMENT.DESCRIPTION: How often invoices will be generated
AD_ELEMENT.HELP: The Invoice Frequency indicates the frequency of invoice generation for a Business Partner.

AD_ELEMENT.NAME: Day of the Week
AD_ELEMENT.HELP: The Invoice Week Day indicates the day of the week to generate invoices.

AD_ELEMENT.NAME: Accrual
AD_ELEMENT.DESCRIPTION: Indicates if Accrual or Cash Based accounting will be used
AD_ELEMENT.HELP: The Accrual checkbox indicates if this accounting schema will use accrual based account or cash based accounting. The Accrual method recognizes revenue when the product or service is delivered. Cash based method recognizes income when then payment is received.

AD_ELEMENT.NAME: Active
AD_ELEMENT.DESCRIPTION: A flag indicating whether this record is available for use or de-activated.
AD_ELEMENT.HELP: There are two methods of making records unavailable in the system: One is to delete the record, the other is to de-activate the record. A de-activated record is not available for selection, but available for reports.There are two reasons for de-activating and not deleting records:(1) The system requires the record for audit purposes.(2) The record is referenced by other records. E.g., you cannot delete a Business Partner, if there are invoices for this partner record existing. You de-activate the Business Partner and prevent that this record is used for future entries.

AD_ELEMENT.NAME: Limit Amount
AD_ELEMENT.DESCRIPTION: Send invoices only if the amount exceeds the limit
AD_ELEMENT.HELP: The Amount Limit checkbox indicates if invoices will be sent out if they are below the entered limit.

AD_ELEMENT.NAME: Amount Approval
AD_ELEMENT.HELP: The Amount Approval checkbox indicates if this approval is an amount approval.

AD_ELEMENT.NAME: Approved
AD_ELEMENT.DESCRIPTION: Indicates if this document requires approval
AD_ELEMENT.HELP: The Approved checkbox indicates if this document requires approval before it can be processed.

AD_ELEMENT.NAME: Activate Audit
AD_ELEMENT.DESCRIPTION: Activate Audit Trail of what numbers are generated
AD_ELEMENT.HELP: The Activate Audit checkbox indicates if an audit trail of numbers generated will be kept.

AD_ELEMENT.NAME: Auto Numbering
AD_ELEMENT.HELP: The Auto Numbering checkbox indicates if the system will assign the next number automatically.

AD_ELEMENT.NAME: Balanced
AD_ELEMENT.HELP: Needs to be balanced.

AD_ELEMENT.NAME: Balancing
AD_ELEMENT.DESCRIPTION: All transactions within an element value must balance (e.g. cost centers)
AD_ELEMENT.HELP: The Balancing checkbox indicates the this element must balance in each journal transaction. For example, if cost centers have been defined as an element which is balance then the debits and credits for each unique cost center must net to 0.00. This is commonly used to define parts of an organization which report as their own entity. Balancing is not an option for the Account element.

AD_ELEMENT.NAME: Base Language
AD_ELEMENT.DESCRIPTION: The system information is maintained in this language
AD_ELEMENT.HELP: The system information is maintained in this language

AD_ELEMENT.NAME: Enforce Batch Control

AD_ELEMENT.NAME: Central Maintenance
AD_ELEMENT.DESCRIPTION: A flag indicating that this label is managed in a central repository.
AD_ELEMENT.HELP: The Centrally Maintained checkbox indicates if the Name, Description and Help maintained in 'System Element' table or 'Window' table.

AD_ELEMENT.NAME: Credit Approved
AD_ELEMENT.HELP: Credit Approved indicates if the credit approval was successful for Orders

AD_ELEMENT.NAME: Customer
AD_ELEMENT.DESCRIPTION: A business partner who will be making purchases.
AD_ELEMENT.HELP: The Customer checkbox indicates if this Business Partner is a customer. If it is select additional fields will display which further define this customer.

AD_ELEMENT.NAME: Deletable Records
AD_ELEMENT.DESCRIPTION: Indicates if records can be deleted from the database
AD_ELEMENT.HELP: The Deleteable Records checkbox indicates if a record can be deleted from the database. If records cannot be deleted, you can only deselect the Active flag

AD_ELEMENT.NAME: Displayed
AD_ELEMENT.DESCRIPTION: Determines, if this field is displayed
AD_ELEMENT.HELP: If the field is displayed, the field Display Logic will determine at runtime, if it is actually displayed

AD_ELEMENT.NAME: Document Controlled
AD_ELEMENT.DESCRIPTION: Control account - If an account is controlled by a document, you cannot post manually to it
AD_ELEMENT.HELP: Control account - If an account is controlled by a document, you cannot post manually to it

AD_ELEMENT.NAME: Sequenced Document
AD_ELEMENT.DESCRIPTION: The document has a document sequence
AD_ELEMENT.HELP: The Document Number Controlled checkbox indicates if this document type will have a sequence number.

AD_ELEMENT.NAME: EMU Member
AD_ELEMENT.DESCRIPTION: This currency is member if the European Monetary Union
AD_ELEMENT.HELP: The Emu Member checkbox is used to indicate if this currency is a member of the European Economic Union.

AD_ELEMENT.NAME: Employee
AD_ELEMENT.DESCRIPTION: A business partner who will be working for an organization.
AD_ELEMENT.HELP: The Employee checkbox indicates if this Business Partner is an Employee. If it is selected, additional fields will display which further identify this employee.

AD_ELEMENT.NAME: Display Encription
AD_ELEMENT.DESCRIPTION: An indication noting if the input box of a field will present full text or just asterisks.
AD_ELEMENT.HELP: Display encryption - all characters are displayed as '*'. Data storage encryption (i.e. you will not be able to report the data via report tools) is set in the Column definition.

AD_ELEMENT.NAME: The Euro Currency
AD_ELEMENT.HELP: The Euro Currency checkbox is used to indicate if this currency is the Euro Currency.

AD_ELEMENT.NAME: Display Field Only
AD_ELEMENT.HELP: The Field Only checkbox indicates that the column will display without a label.

AD_ELEMENT.NAME: Fully Qualified
AD_ELEMENT.HELP: The Fully Qualified check box indicates that all required elements for an account combination are present.

AD_ELEMENT.NAME: Generated

AD_ELEMENT.NAME: Display Label Only

AD_ELEMENT.NAME: Identifier

AD_ELEMENT.NAME: Accounting Tab

AD_ELEMENT.NAME: Re-invoice

AD_ELEMENT.NAME: Key Column

AD_ELEMENT.NAME: Mandatory
AD_ELEMENT.DESCRIPTION: An indication noting that completing in a field is required to proceed.
AD_ELEMENT.HELP: The Mandatory checkbox indicates if the field is required for a record to be save to the database.

AD_ELEMENT.NAME: Natural Account
AD_ELEMENT.HELP: The natural account is often based on (industry specific) chart of accounts

AD_ELEMENT.NAME: Link to Parent Column
AD_ELEMENT.DESCRIPTION: This column is a link to the parent table (e.g. header from lines) - incl. Association key columns

AD_ELEMENT.NAME: Primary

AD_ELEMENT.NAME: Print
AD_ELEMENT.DESCRIPTION: A reference stating whether or not the document has been printed at any time in the past.

AD_ELEMENT.NAME: Processing

AD_ELEMENT.NAME: Product Attribute Approval
AD_ELEMENT.DESCRIPTION: Approval is based on a product attribute
AD_ELEMENT.HELP: The Product Attribute Approval checkbox indicates if this approval is a product attribute approval.

AD_ELEMENT.NAME: Potential Customer

AD_ELEMENT.NAME: Purchase

AD_ELEMENT.NAME: Range

AD_ELEMENT.HELP: The Range checkbox indicates that this parameter is a range of values.

AD_ELEMENT.NAME: Read Only

AD_ELEMENT.NAME: Editable Field

AD_ELEMENT.NAME: Sales Price List

AD_ELEMENT.NAME: Sales Representative

AD_ELEMENT.NAME: Display on Same Line

AD_ELEMENT.NAME: Security enabled

AD_ELEMENT.NAME: Default Edit Mode

AD_ELEMENT.NAME: Stocked

AD_ELEMENT.NAME: System Language
AD_ELEMENT.DESCRIPTION: The screens, etc. are maintained in this Language
AD_ELEMENT.HELP: Select, if you want to have translated screens available in this language. Please notify your system administrator to run the language maintenance scripts to enable the use of this language. If the language is not supplied, you can translate the terms yourself.

AD_ELEMENT.NAME: Used for Record ID

AD_ELEMENT.NAME: Transferred

AD_ELEMENT.NAME: Translation

AD_ELEMENT.NAME: Translation Tab

AD_ELEMENT.NAME: Updatable

AD_ELEMENT.NAME: User updateable
AD_ELEMENT.DESCRIPTION: The field can be updated by the user
AD_ELEMENT.HELP: The User Updateable checkbox indicate if the user can update this field.

AD_ELEMENT.NAME: Vendor
AD_ELEMENT.DESCRIPTION: A business partner who sells products or services.
AD_ELEMENT.HELP: The Vendor checkbox indicates if this Business Partner is a Vendor. If it is selected, additional fields will display which further identify this vendor.

AD_ELEMENT.NAME: Workflow Approval
AD_ELEMENT.DESCRIPTION: This approval is used in workflow
AD_ELEMENT.HELP: The Workflow Approval checkbox indicates if this approval is a workflow approval. If it is selected a drop down list box will display for selection of a specific workflow.

AD_ELEMENT.NAME: Last Contact Date
AD_ELEMENT.DESCRIPTION: Date this individual was last contacted
AD_ELEMENT.HELP: The Last Contact indicates the date that this Business Partner Contact was last contacted.

AD_ELEMENT.NAME: Last Contact Result
AD_ELEMENT.DESCRIPTION: A statement related to the result of the last interaction with a business partner.
AD_ELEMENT.HELP: The Last Result identifies the result of the last contact made.

AD_ELEMENT.NAME: Maximum Level
AD_ELEMENT.DESCRIPTION: Maximum Inventory level for this product
AD_ELEMENT.HELP: Indicates the maximum quantity of this product to be stocked in inventory.

AD_ELEMENT.NAME: Minimum Level
AD_ELEMENT.DESCRIPTION: Minimum Inventory level for this product
AD_ELEMENT.HELP: Indicates the minimum quantity of this product to be stocked in inventory.

AD_ELEMENT.NAME: Line No.
AD_ELEMENT.DESCRIPTION: A line stating the position of this request in the document.
AD_ELEMENT.HELP: Indicates the unique line for a document. It will also control the display order of the lines within a document.

AD_ELEMENT.NAME: Line Net Amount
AD_ELEMENT.DESCRIPTION: The final amount of a specified line, based only on quantities and prices.
AD_ELEMENT.HELP: Indicates the line net amount based on the quantity and the actual price. Any additional charges or freight are not included.

AD_ELEMENT.NAME: Seq. of Introduced Tables

AD_ELEMENT.NAME: Lot

AD_ELEMENT.HELP: The Lot Number indicates the specific lot that a product was part of.

AD_ELEMENT.NAME: Storage Bin

AD_ELEMENT.HELP: The Locator ID indicates where in a Warehouse a product is located.

AD_ELEMENT.NAME: Price List
AD_ELEMENT.DESCRIPTION: A catalog of selected items with prices defined generally or for a specific partner.
AD_ELEMENT.HELP: Price Lists are used to determine the pricing, margin and cost of items purchased or sold.

AD_ELEMENT.NAME: Price List Version
AD_ELEMENT.DESCRIPTION: A price list with a specified validity range.
AD_ELEMENT.HELP: Each Price List can have multiple versions. The most common use is to indicate the dates that a Price List is valid for.

AD_ELEMENT.NAME: Product Category
AD_ELEMENT.DESCRIPTION: A classification of items based on similar characteristics or attributes.
AD_ELEMENT.HELP: Identifies the category which this product belongs to. Product categories are used for pricing.

AD_ELEMENT.NAME: Product
AD_ELEMENT.DESCRIPTION: An item produced by a process.
AD_ELEMENT.HELP: Identifies an item which is either purchased or sold in this organization.

AD_ELEMENT.NAME: Shipping Company
AD_ELEMENT.DESCRIPTION: The name of the company making the shipment.
AD_ELEMENT.HELP: The Shipper is any entity which will provide shipping to or shipping from an Organization.

AD_ELEMENT.NAME: Service Point
AD_ELEMENT.DESCRIPTION: The location where products arrive to or are sent from.
AD_ELEMENT.HELP: The Warehouse identifies a unique Warehouse where products are stored or Services are provided.

AD_ELEMENT.NAME: Message Text
AD_ELEMENT.DESCRIPTION: The text/content of the spplication initiated message.
AD_ELEMENT.HELP: The Message Text indicates the message that will display

AD_ELEMENT.NAME: Hint
AD_ELEMENT.DESCRIPTION: A help or advice provided regarding the application initiated message.
AD_ELEMENT.HELP: The Message Tip defines additional help or information about this message.

AD_ELEMENT.NAME: Message Type
AD_ELEMENT.DESCRIPTION: Type of message (Informational, Menu or Error)
AD_ELEMENT.HELP: The Message Type indicates the type of message being defined. Valid message types are Informational, Menu and Error.

AD_ELEMENT.NAME: Multiple Rate by
AD_ELEMENT.DESCRIPTION: The rate by which the base unit will be mutiplied by to create the converted unit.
AD_ELEMENT.HELP: To convert Source number to Target number, the Source is multiplied by the multiply rate. If the Multiply Rate is entered, then the Divide Rate will be automatically calculated.

AD_ELEMENT.NAME: NAICS/SIC

AD_ELEMENT.NAME: Name

AD_ELEMENT.NAME: Overdue Payment Days Rule

AD_ELEMENT.NAME: Node_ID

AD_ELEMENT.NAME: No. of Employees

AD_ELEMENT.NAME: OS Command

AD_ELEMENT.NAME: Organization

AD_ELEMENT.NAME: Period Action
AD_ELEMENT.HELP: The Period Action indicates the action to be taken for this period. For example 'Close Period' or 'Open Period'.

AD_ELEMENT.NAME: Period No.

AD_ELEMENT.NAME: Period Status
AD_ELEMENT.HELP: The Period Status indicates the current status for this period. For example 'Closed', 'Open', 'Never Opened'.

AD_ELEMENT.NAME: Period Type
AD_ELEMENT.HELP: The Period Type indicates the type (Standard or Adjustment) of period.

AD_ELEMENT.NAME: Future Days

AD_ELEMENT.NAME: History Days

History Days enable to post to previous periods. E.g. today is May 15th and History Days is set to 30, you can post back to April 15th

AD_ELEMENT.NAME: Phone

AD_ELEMENT.NAME: Priority

AD_ELEMENT.NAME: Process Now

AD_ELEMENT.NAME: Region Name

AD_ELEMENT.NAME: Replenishment Type

AD_ELEMENT.NAME: Retained Earning

AD_ELEMENT.NAME: Sales Campaign

AD_ELEMENT.NAME: Marketing Channel

AD_ELEMENT.NAME: Credit Limit

AD_ELEMENT.NAME: Credit Used

AD_ELEMENT.NAME: Delivery Terms

AD_ELEMENT.NAME: Sales Order

AD_ELEMENT.PO_HELP: The Purchase Order ID is a unique identifier of a Purchase Order. This is controlled by the document sequence for this document type.

AD_ELEMENT.NAME: Invoice Terms

AD_ELEMENT.NAME: Invoice Schedule

AD_ELEMENT.NAME: Sales Order Line

AD_ELEMENT.PO_HELP: The Purchase Order Line is a unique identifier for a line in an order.

AD_ELEMENT.NAME: Volume of Sales

AD_ELEMENT.NAME: Storage Bin Separator

AD_ELEMENT.NAME: Share

AD_ELEMENT.NAME: Shelf Depth

AD_ELEMENT.NAME: Shelf Height
AD_ELEMENT.HELP: The Shelf Height indicates the height dimension required on a shelf for a product

AD_ELEMENT.NAME: Shelf Width

AD_ELEMENT.NAME: Record Sort No.

AD_ELEMENT.NAME: Starting Date

AD_ELEMENT.NAME: Restart sequence every Year

AD_ELEMENT.NAME: Starting No.

AD_ELEMENT.NAME: Standard Precision

AD_ELEMENT.NAME: Substitute Product

AD_ELEMENT.HELP: The Substitute identifies the product to be used as a substitute for this product.

AD_ELEMENT.NAME: Suffix

AD_ELEMENT.NAME: Units Per Pallet

AD_ELEMENT.NAME: Weight

AD_ELEMENT.NAME: Level (Z)

AD_ELEMENT.NAME: Partner Bank Account

AD_ELEMENT.NAME: Withholding
AD_ELEMENT.HELP: The Withholding indicates the type of withholding to be calculated.

AD_ELEMENT.NAME: Charge Amount
AD_ELEMENT.DESCRIPTION: The amount of a cost or expense incurred during business activity.

AD_ELEMENT.NAME: Direct shipment

AD_ELEMENT.NAME: Document Category

AD_ELEMENT.NAME: Number of Copies

AD_ELEMENT.NAME: Comments

AD_ELEMENT.NAME: Email

AD_ELEMENT.NAME: Enforce Price Limit
AD_ELEMENT.DESCRIPTION: Do not allow prices below the limit price
AD_ELEMENT.HELP: The Enforce Price Limit check box indicates that prices cannot be below the limit price in Orders. Invoices are not checked.

AD_ELEMENT.NAME: Exempt Reason

AD_ELEMENT.NAME: Fee Amount

AD_ELEMENT.NAME: Fix Amount
AD_ELEMENT.DESCRIPTION: Fix amounted amount to be levied or paid
AD_ELEMENT.HELP: The Fixed Amount indicates a fixed amount to be levied or paid.

AD_ELEMENT.NAME: Last Day Cut-off
AD_ELEMENT.DESCRIPTION: Last day to include for next due date

AD_ELEMENT.NAME: Maturity Date 1
AD_ELEMENT.DESCRIPTION: The day of the month that invoices are due. 3 maturity dates can be defined.

AD_ELEMENT.NAME: Grace Days
AD_ELEMENT.DESCRIPTION: Days after due date to send first dunning letter
AD_ELEMENT.HELP: The Grace Days indicates the number of days after the due date to send the first dunning letter. This field displays only if the send dunning letters checkbox has been selected.

AD_ELEMENT.NAME: Import Error Message
AD_ELEMENT.DESCRIPTION: A message that appears when errors occur during the importing process.

AD_ELEMENT.NAME: Bill to Address

AD_ELEMENT.NAME: Fixed Due Date
AD_ELEMENT.DESCRIPTION: Payment is due on a fixed date

AD_ELEMENT.NAME: Foreign Currency Account

AD_ELEMENT.NAME: Mandatory Withholding

AD_ELEMENT.NAME: Own Bank

AD_ELEMENT.NAME: Payment to External Party

AD_ELEMENT.HELP: The Paid to Third Party checkbox indicates that the amounts are paid to someone other than the Business Partner.

AD_ELEMENT.NAME: Same Tax

AD_ELEMENT.NAME: Ship to Address
AD_ELEMENT.DESCRIPTION: Business Partner address to ship goods to
AD_ELEMENT.HELP: The Ship to Address checkbox indicates if this location is the address to use when shipping orders to this Business Partner.

AD_ELEMENT.NAME: Prorate Tax

AD_ELEMENT.NAME: Tax Withholding

AD_ELEMENT.NAME: Min. Amount

AD_ELEMENT.NAME: SO Sub Type
AD_ELEMENT.HELP:
The SO Sub Type indicates the type of sales order this document refers to. This field only appears when the Document Base Type is Sales Order. The selection made here will determine which documents will be generated when an order is processed and which documents must be generated manually or in batches.
The following outlines this process.
SO Sub Type of Standard Order will generate just the Order document when the order is processed.
The Delivery Note, Invoice and Receipt must be generated via other processes.
SO Sub Type of Warehouse Order will generate the Order and Delivery Note.
The Invoice and Receipt must be generated via other processes.
SO Sub Type of Credit Order will generate the Order, Delivery Note and Invoice.
The Reciept must be generated via other processes.
SO Sub Type of POS (Point of Sale) will generate all document
